HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1260
By Warner
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Josie Brown of Forrest
High School on being named a Distinguished
Tennessean Scholar.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to excellence,
have distinguished themselves in the classroom and beyond; and
WHEREAS, Josie Brown of Marshall County is one such exceptional student, who was
recently named a recipient of the prestigious Distinguished Tennessean Scholarship, a highly
competitive award that covers tuition and fees for four years at the University of Tennessee,
Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, a student at Forrest High School, Josie Brown has distinguished herself
through exceptional academic achievement, leadership, and involvement and will graduate
summa cum laude, ranking in the Top 10 in her class; and
WHEREAS, a leader among her peers, Ms. Brown serves as Senior Class President
and Student Council President and is the senior editor of the school year book, in which
capacity she has played a key role in capturing and preserving student life; and
WHEREAS, she was selected to represent Forrest High School as a delegate to ALA
Volunteer Girls State, an honor recognizing young women for their leadership, character, and
dedication to civic responsibility; and
WHEREAS, an athlete as well as a scholar, Ms. Brown was a four-year varsity athlete in
both volleyball and basketball, having demonstrated teamwork, discipline, and perseverance
throughout her high school career; and
WHEREAS, her noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for her family,
her school, and her community; and
HJR1260
016971
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Josie Brown's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we commend and honor Josie Brown on being named a Distinguished
Tennessean Scholar and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
